Zimbabwean journalist and documentary filmmaker Hopewell Chin'ono. AFP/Jekesai Njikizana HARARE - Zimbabwean journalist Hopewell Chin'ono has been arrested, yet again.
He claims he's being charged with communicating false information. READ:Â Chin'ono 'committed to work' despite arrests That's after he reported that a child died after being beaten up by a police officer. Chin'ono has been taken to Harare's Central Police Station. The journalist recently spent time in prison in Zimbabwe on charges of inciting violence and obstructing justice.